.TEXT,SETS
834,0,Benefit Enrollment and Maintenance
834,1,BE
834,2,This X12 Transaction Set contains the format and establishes the data contents of the Benefit Enrollment and Maintenance Transaction Set \040834\041 for use within the context of an Electronic Data Interchange \040EDI\041 environment\046 This transaction set can be used to establish communication between the sponsor of the insurance product and the payer\046 Such transaction\040s\041 may or may not take place through a third party administrator \040TPA\041\046 For the purpose of this standard\044 the sponsor is the party or entity that ultimately pays for the coverage\044 benefit or product\046 A sponsor can be an employer\044 union\044 government agency\044 association\044 or insurance agency\046 The payer refers to an entity that pays claims\044 administers the insurance product or benefit\044 or both\046 A payer can be an insurance company\044 health maintenance organization \040HMO\041\044 preferred provider organization \040PPO\041\044 government agency \040Medicare\044 Medicaid\044 Champus\044 etc\046\041\044 or an entity that may be contracted by one of these former groups\046 For the purpose of the 834 transaction set\044 a third party administrator \040TPA\041 can be contracted by a sponsor to handle data gathering from those covered by the sponsor if the sponsor does not elect to perform this function itself\046 
834,4,005010X220A1\044 Benefit Enrollment and Maintenance \040834\041
834~1,7,ST\042834\0420001\042005010X220A1\126
834~108,3,Custodial Parent
834~108,4,Required when the custodial parent of a minor dependent is someone other than the subscriber\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
834~108,5,1\046 Any other situation\044 \040examples\058 Guardianship\044 Legal Indemnity\044 Power of Attorney\044 and\047or Separation Agreements\041 would be handled under the Responsible Party NM1 segment\046
