834~221~2,14,The transaction set control numbers in ST02 and SE02 must be identical\046 This unique number also aids in error resolution research\046 For example\044 start with the number 0001 and increment from there\046 This number must be unique within a specific group and interchange\044 but the number can repeat in other groups and interchanges\046
834~2~1~00~1~0,0,If the original transaction has already been processed\044 an incoming transaction using this code may be rejected by the receiver\046 The rejection will be identified to the sender by telephone or other direct contact\046\r\nThe \14700\148 indicates the first time the transaction is sent\046
834~2~1~15~1~0,0,Send the \145\14515\146\146 when the original transmission was incorrect\044 has yet to be processed by the receiver\044 and a new corrected transmission is being sent\046 This transmission can then be pended by the receiver\146s translator for further review\046
834~2~1~22~1~0,0,Send the \145\14522\146\146 when the original transmission was lost or not processed\044 and the sender is passing another transmission that is the same as the original\046
834~2~2,1,Transaction Set Reference Number
834~2~2,14,This element is the transaction set reference number assigned by the sender\146s application\046 It uniquely identifies this occurrence of the transaction for future reference\046
