834~43,0,A Subscriber is a person who elects the benefits and is affiliated with the employer or the insurer\046 A Dependent is a person who is affiliated with the subscriber\044 such as a spouse\044 child\044 etc\046\044 and is therefore entitled to benefits\046 Subscriber information must come before dependent information\046 The INS segment is used to note if information being submitted is subscriber information or dependent information\046
834~43,3,Member Level Detail
834~43,5,1\046 Subscriber information must preceed dependent information in a transmission\044 or the subscriber information must have been submitted to the receiver in a previous transmission\046
