.TEXT,SEGS
ACT,0,Account Identification
ACT,1,To specify account information
ACT~0,1,ACT02 is the name of the account in ACT01\046\r\n\r\nACT07 is the name associated with the account identified in ACT06\046\r\n\r\n
ACT~0,2,ACT06 is an account associated with the account in ACT01\046\r\n\r\nACT08 indicates if the data for the account in ACT01 is used for billing or information purposes\046\r\n\r\n
AD1,0,Adjustment Amount
AD1,1,To specify the characteristics of an adjustment
AD1~0,1,AD102 is the adjustment amount\046\r\n\r\nAD104 is frequency of the AD102 monetary amount\046\r\n\r\n
AIN,0,Income
AIN,1,To provide type and amount of income obtained
AIN~0,1,AIN01 defines the nature or source of income earned\046\r\n\r\nAIN02 defines the periodicity of the income amount\046\r\n\r\nAIN03 defines amount of income\046\r\n\r\nAIN04 specifies number of scheduled periods or year of income receipt\046\r\n\r\nAIN05 identifies if the employee\039s income is expected to continue in lieu of compensation benefits\046 A \034Y\034 indicates income is expected to continue\059 an \034N\034 indicates income is not expected to continue\046\r\n\r\nAIN06 is used to identify an internal control number\046\r\n\r\nAIN07 indicates the income being identified in this segment is a net amount\044 a gross amount\044 or other amount\046\r\n\r\nAIN08 identifies the tax status or treatment of the amount specified in AIN03\046\r\n\r\nAIN11 identifies the number of units of time at which the rate specified in AIN09 applies\046\r\n\r\nAIN12 identifies the American Payroll Association Code to be used to identify the specific income type for payroll payments\046\r\n\r\nAIN13 further describes the type of income identified in AIN12\046\r\n\r\n
AMT,0,Monetary Amount Information
AMT,1,To indicate the total monetary amount
BEN,0,Beneficiary or Owner Information
BEN,1,To supply beneficiary\044 co\045participant\044 and owner information
BEN~0,1,BEN02 is the percent of benefits that the beneficiary will receive\046\r\n\r\nBEN04 is the employee signature on file indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the employee signature has been obtained and is on file\059 an \034N\034 value indicates the employee signature has not been obtained\046\r\n\r\nBEN05 is spouse signature on file indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the spouse signature has been obtained and is on file\059 an \034N\034 value indicates the spouse signature has not been obtained\046\r\n\r\n
BGN,0,Beginning Segment
BGN,1,To indicate the beginning of a transaction set
BGN~0,1,BGN02 is the transaction set reference number\046\r\n\r\nBGN03 is the transaction set date\046\r\n\r\nBGN04 is the transaction set time\046\r\n\r\nBGN05 is the transaction set time qualifier\046\r\n\r\nBGN06 is the transaction set reference number of a previously sent transaction affected by the current transaction\046\r\n\r\n
COB,0,Coordination of Benefits
COB,1,To supply information on coordination of benefits
COB,2,Required whenever an individual has another insurance plan with benefits similar to those covered by the insurance product specified in the HD segment for this occurrence of Loop ID\0452300\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
COB~0,1,COB02 is the policy number\046\r\n\r\n
DMG,0,Demographic Information
DMG,1,To supply demographic information
DMG~0,1,DMG02 is the date of birth\046\r\n\r\nDMG07 is the country of citizenship\046\r\n\r\nDMG09 is the age in years\046\r\n\r\nDMG11 is used to specify how the information in DMG05\044 including repeats of C056\044 was collected\046\r\n\r\n
DSB,0,Disability Information
DSB,1,To supply disability information
DSB,2,Required when enrolling a disabled member or when disability information about an existing member is added or changed\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
DSB~0,1,DSB02 is scheduled work days before the disability\046\r\n\r\nDSB06 is the maximum amount of disability coverage to which the insured is entitled\046\r\n\r\nDSB08 is the functional status code for the disability\046\r\n\r\n
DTP,0,Date or Time or Period
DTP,1,To specify any or all of a date\044 a time\044 or a time period
DTP~0,1,DTP02 is the date or time or period format that will appear in DTP03\046\r\n\r\n
EC,0,Employment Class
EC,1,To provide class of employment information
EC~0,1,EC04 is percent of ownership\046\r\n\r\nEC05 applies to the entire segment\046\r\n\r\n
ENT,0,Entity
ENT,1,To designate the entities which are parties to a transaction and specify a reference meaningful to those entities
ENT~0,2,This segment allows for the grouping of data by entity\047entities at or within a master\047masters\046 A master \040e\046g\046\044 an organization\041 can be comprised of numerous subgroups \040e\046g\046\044 entities\041\046 This master may send grouped data to another master \040e\046g\046\044 an organization\041 which is comprised of one or more entities\046 Groupings are as follows\058\r\n\r\n\0401\041 Single\047Single\058 Only ENT01 is necessary\044 because there is a single entity \040the sending master\041 communicating with a single entity \040the receiving master\041\046\r\n\r\n\0402\041 Single\047Multiple\058 ENT05\044 ENT06\044 and ENT07 would be used to identify the entities within the receiving master\046 The sending master is a single entity\044 so no other data elements need be used\046\r\n\r\n\0403\041 Multiple\047Single\058 ENT02\044 ENT03\044 and ENT04 would be used to identify the entities within the sending master\046 The receiving master is a single entity\044 so no other data elements need be used\046\r\n\r\n\0404\041 Multiple\047Multiple\058 ENT02\044 ENT03\044 and ENT04 would be used to identify the entities within the sending master\046 ENT05\044 ENT06\044 and ENT07 would be used to identify the entities within the receiving master\046\r\n\r\nThis segment also allows for the transmission of a unique reference number that is meaningful between the entities\046\r\n\r\n
FC,0,Financial Contribution
FC,1,To specify the financial contribution information
FC~0,1,FC02 is the percent of salary an employee elects to contribute\046\r\n\r\nFC03 is the dollar amount of the contribution\046\r\n\r\nFC04 is the number of payments per year\046\r\n\r\nFC05 is the billing indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates that the participant is billed for this type of money\059 an \034N\034 value indicates that the participant is not billed for this type of money\046\r\n\r\n
FSA,0,Flexible Spending Account
FSA,1,To supply flexible spending account information
FSA~0,1,FSA04 is the flexible spending account \040FSA\041 policy number\046\r\n\r\nFSA05 specifies the frequency of contribution\046\r\n\r\n
HD,0,Health Coverage
HD,1,To provide information on health coverage
HD~0,1,HD06 is the number of collateral dependents for the primary insured\046 A collateral dependent is a relative related by blood or marriage who resides in the home and is dependent on the employee for support\046\r\n\r\nHD07 is the number of sponsored dependents for the primary insured\046 A sponsored dependent is a dependent between the ages of 19 and 25 who is not in school\046\r\n\r\nHD09 is a late enrollee indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the insured is a late enrollee\044 which can result in a reduction of benefits\059 an \034N\034 value indicates the insured is a regular enrollee\046\r\n\r\nHD11 is a prescription drug service coverage indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates that prescription drug service coverage applies\059 an \034N\034 value indicates that prescription drug service coverage does not apply\046\r\n\r\n
HI,0,Health Care Information Codes
HI,1,To supply information related to the delivery of health care
HLH,0,Health Information
HLH,1,To provide health information
HLH~0,1,HLH03 is the current weight in pounds\046\r\n\r\nHLH04 is the previous weight in pounds\046\r\n\r\nHLH05 is the reason for change in weight\046\r\n\r\nHLH07 describes the reason for last doctor visit\046\r\n\r\n
ICM,0,Individual Income
ICM,1,To supply information to determine benefit eligibility\044 deductibles\044 and retirement and investment contributions
ICM~0,1,ICM01 is the frequency at which an individual\039s wages are paid\046\r\n\r\nICM02 is the yearly wages amount\046\r\n\r\nICM03 is the weekly hours\046\r\n\r\nICM04 is the employer location qualifier such as a department number\046\r\n\r\n
IDC,0,Identification Card
IDC,1,To provide notification to produce replacement identification card\040s\041
IDC~0,1,IDC03 is the number of cards being requested\046\r\n\r\nIDC04 is the reason for the card being requested\044 i\046e\046\044 add or a change\046\r\n\r\n
INS,0,Insured Benefit
INS,1,To provide benefit information on insured entities
INS~0,1,INS01 indicates status of the insured\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the insured is a subscriber\058 an \034N\034 value indicates the insured is a dependent\046\r\n\r\nINS10 is the handicapped status indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates an individual is handicapped\059 an \034N\034 value indicates an individual is not handicapped\046\r\n\r\nINS12 is the date of death\046\r\n\r\nINS14\044 INS15\044 and INS16 identify where the employee works\046\r\n\r\nINS17 is the number assigned to each family member born with the same birth date\046 This number identifies birth sequence for multiple births allowing proper tracking and response of benefits for each dependent \040i\046e\046\044 twins\044 triplets\044 etc\046\041\046\r\n\r\n
INV,0,Investment Vehicle Selection
INV,1,To specify type of investment vehicle or account and other basic data about the investment
INV~0,1,INV01 is the investment fund description of the \034receiving\034 or \034to\034 investment fund\046\r\n\r\nINV02 is the percent of contribution amount to be deposited into the investment fund described in INV01\046\r\n\r\nINV03 is the dollar amount to be deposited into the investment fund described in INV01\046\r\n\r\nINV04 is the number of units or shares to be invested in the investment fund described in INV01\046\r\n\r\nINV05 is the state of sale for the investment fund described in INV01\046\r\n\r\nINV06 is the \034originating\034 or \034from\034 investment fund description for an interfund transfer\046\r\n\r\nINV07 is the current balance of the investment fund described in INV01\046\r\n\r\n
K3,0,File Information
K3,1,To transmit a fixed\045format record or matrix contents
K3~0,1,K303 identifies the value of the index\046\r\n\r\n
K3~0,2,The default for K302 is content\046\r\n\r\n
LC,0,Life Coverage
LC,1,To provide information on life coverage
LC~0,1,LC05 is the salary multiplier\046\r\n\r\nLC07 is the employee signature on file indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the employee signature has been obtained and is on file\059 an \034N\034 value indicates the employee signature has not been obtained\046\r\n\r\n
LE,0,Loop Trailer
LE,1,To indicate that the loop immediately preceding this segment is complete
LE~0,1,One loop may be nested contained within another loop\044 provided the inner nested loop terminates before the other loop\046 When specified by the standards setting body as mandatory\044 this segment in combination with \034LS\034\044 must be used\046 It is not to be used if not specifically set forth for use\046 The loop identifier in the loop header and trailer must be identical\046 The value for the identifier is the loop ID of the required loop beginning segment\046 The loop ID number is given on the transaction set diagram in the appropriate ASC X12 version\047release\046\r\n\r\n
LE~0,2,See Figures Appendix for an explanation of the use of the LE and LS segments\046\r\n\r\n
LS,0,Loop Header
LS,1,To indicate that the next segment begins a loop
LS~0,1,One loop may be nested contained within another loop\044 provided the inner nested loop terminates before the outer loop\046 When specified by the standard setting body as mandatory\044 this segment in combination with \034LE\034\044 must be used\046 It is not to be used if not specifically set forth for use\046 The loop identifier in the loop header and trailer must be identical\046 The value for the identifier is the loop ID of the required loop segment\046 The loop ID number is given on the transaction set diagram in the appropriate ASC X12 version\047release\046\r\n\r\n
LS~0,2,See Figures Appendix for an explanation of the use of the LS and LE segments\046\r\n\r\n
LUI,0,Language Use
LUI,1,To specify language\044 type of usage\044 and proficiency or fluency
LUI~0,1,LUI02 is the language code\046\r\n\r\nLUI03 is the name of the language\046\r\n\r\n
LX,0,Transaction Set Line Number
LX,1,To reference a line number in a transaction set
N1,0,Party Identification
N1,1,To identify a party by type of organization\044 name\044 and code
N1~0,2,This segment\044 used alone\044 provides the most efficient method of providing organizational identification\046 To obtain this efficiency the \034ID Code\034 \040N104\041 must provide a key to the table maintained by the transaction processing party\046\r\n\r\nN105 and N106 further define the type of entity in N101\046\r\n\r\n
N2,0,Additional Name Information
N2,1,To specify additional names
N3,0,Party Location
N3,1,To specify the location of the named party
N4,0,Geographic Location
N4,1,To specify the geographic place of the named party
N4~0,2,A combination of either N401 through N404\044 or N405 and N406 may be adequate to specify a location\046\r\n\r\nN402 is required only if city name \040N401\041 is in the U\046S\046 or Canada\046\r\n\r\n
NM1,0,Individual or Organizational Name
NM1,1,To supply the full name of an individual or organizational entity
NM1~0,1,NM102 qualifies NM103\046\r\n\r\n
NM1~0,2,NM110 and NM111 further define the type of entity in NM101\046\r\n\r\nNM112 can identify a second surname\046\r\n\r\n
NX1,0,Property or Entity Identification
NX1,1,To define the attributes of a property or an entity
PER,0,Administrative Communications Contact
PER,1,To identify a person or office to whom administrative communications should be directed
PER,2,Required when detailed COB coverage information is agreed to be exchanged\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
PLA,0,Place or Location
PLA,1,To indicate action to be taken for the location specified and to qualify the location specified
PLA~0,1,PLA03 is the effective date for the action identified in PLA01\046\r\n\r\nWhen used\044 PLA04 is the effective time for the action identified in PLA01\046\r\n\r\n
PM,0,Electronic Funds Transfer Information
PM,1,To supply information on the electronic funds transfer \040EFT\041 method of payment
PM~0,1,PM01 is the transit routing number of the receiving financial institution\046\r\n\r\nPM02 is the electronic fund transfer recipient\039s account number\046\r\n\r\nPM03 is the authorization for electronic funds transfer indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates authorization has been granted to allow electronic funds transfer\059 an \034N\034 value indicates no authorization has been granted for electronic funds transfer\046\r\n\r\nPM04 is the authorization signature for electronic funds transfer on file indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates that a signature has been obtained and is on file\059 an \034N\034 value indicates a signature has not been obtained\046\r\n\r\nPM05 qualifies the account number indicated in PM02\046\r\n\r\nPM06 qualifies the Depository Financial Institution \040DFI\041 Identification Number indicated in PM01\046\r\n\r\n
PRV,0,Provider Information
PRV,1,To specify the identifying characteristics of a provider
QTY,0,Quantity Information
QTY,1,To specify quantity information
QTY~0,1,QTY04 is used when the quantity is non\045numeric\046\r\n\r\n
REF,0,Reference Information
REF,1,To specify identifying information
REF~0,1,REF04 contains data relating to the value cited in REF02\046\r\n\r\n
REL,0,Relationship
REL,1,To specify relationship and birth order of entity
REL~0,1,REL02 is an ordinal number indicating birth order\046\r\n\r\n
RP,0,Retirement Product
RP,1,To specify the retirement product characteristics
RP~0,1,RP06 is the eligibility indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the participant is eligible for plan allocations\059 an \034N\034 value indicates the participant is not eligible for plan allocations\046\r\n\r\nRP08 specifies the authorizations granted for transfer of funds via the telephone\046\r\n\r\n
SE,0,Transaction Set Trailer
SE,1,To indicate the end of the transaction set and provide the count of the transmitted segments \040including the beginning \040ST\041 and ending \040SE\041 segments\041
SE~0,2,SE is the last segment of each transaction set\046\r\n\r\n
ST,0,Transaction Set Header
ST,1,To indicate the start of a transaction set and to assign a control number
ST,4,ST\042834\0420001\126
ST~0,1,The transaction set identifier \040ST01\041 is used by the translation routines of the interchange partners to select the appropriate transaction set definition \040e\046g\046\044 810 selects the Invoice Transaction Set\041\046\r\n\r\nThe implementation convention reference \040ST03\041 is used by the translation routines of the interchange partners to select the appropriate implementation convention to match the transaction set definition\046  When used\044 this implementation convention reference takes precedence over the implementation reference specified in the GS08\046\r\n\r\n
.TEXT,COMS
C001,0,Composite Unit of Measure
C001,1,To identify a composite unit of measure \040See Figures Appendix for examples of use\041 
C001~0,2,If C001\04502 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04503 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04505 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04506 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04508 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04509 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04511 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04512 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04514 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\nIf C001\04515 is not used\044 its value is to be interpreted as 1\046\r\n
C022,0,Health Care Code Information
C022,1,To send health care codes and their associated dates\044 amounts and quantities 
C022~0,1,C022\04501 qualifies C022\04502\044 C022\04504\044 C022\04505\044 C022\04506 and C022\04508\046\r\nIf C022\04508 is used\044 then C022\04502 represents the beginning value in a range of \r\ncodes\046\r\nC022\04503 is the date format that will appear in C022\04504\046\r\nC022\04507 qualifies C022\04501\046\r\nC022\04508 represents the ending value in a range of codes\046\r\nC022\04509 is used to identify the diagnosis onset as it relates to the diagnosis \r\nreported in C022\04502\046  A \034Y\034 indicates that the onset occurred prior to \r\nadmission to the hospital\059 an \034N\034 indicates that the onset did NOT occur prior \r\nto admission to the hospital\059 a \034U\034 indicates that it is unknown whether the \r\nonset occurred prior to admission to the hospital or not\046\r\n
C022~0,2,C022\04509 would only need to be reported to data collectors requiring this \r\ninformation when C022\04501 is \034BF\034 \040Diagnosis Code\041 and range of diagnosis codes \r\nwere NOT given in C022\04508\046\r\n
C035,0,Provider Specialty Information
C035,1,To provide provider specialty information 
C035~0,1,C035\04502 qualifies C035\04501\046\r\nC035\04503 is the provider specialty certification indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value \r\nindicates the provider is certified in the specialty indicated\046 An \034N\034 value \r\nindicates the provider is not certified in the specialty indicated\046 A \034U\034 value \r\nindicates that it is unknown whether the provider is certified in the specialty \r\nindicated\046\r\n
C040,0,Reference Identifier
C040,1,To identify one or more reference numbers or identification numbers as specified by the Reference Qualifier 
C052,0,Medicare Status Code
C052,1,To provide Medicare coverage and associated reason for Medicare eligibility 
C052,2,Required if a member is being enrolled or disenrolled in Medicare\044 is currently in Medicare or has terminated or changed their Medicare enrollment\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
C056,0,Composite Race or Ethnicity Information
C056,1,To send general and detailed information on race or ethnicity 
C056,2,Required when such transmission is required under the insurance contract between the sponsor and payer and allowed by federal and state regulations\046 If not required by this\r\nimplementation guide\044 do not send\046
C056~0,1,C056\04502 and C056\04503 are used to specify detailed information about race or \r\nethnicity\046\r\n
